entry.title: U.N. Team Arrives in Zaporizhzhia Ahead of Nuclear-Plant Inspection
entry.content: An International Atomic Energy Agency team arrived in the Ukrainian city of Zaporizhzhia ahead of an inspection of the nearby Russian-occupied nuclear-power plant.

entry.title: China's Economic Woes Drag On With Factory Disruptions, Property Slump
entry.content: Extreme weather and power shortages depressed manufacturing, while home sales fell for the 14th consecutive month.

entry.title: Mikhail Gorbachev, Reformer of Soviet Union, Dies at 91
entry.content: The architect of “perestroika” and “glasnost”—restructuring and openness—unleashed a wave of unstoppable forces that led to the bloc’s demise in 1991.
